@node FUTURE "Future"

@{b}@{u}pEditor's todos@{uu}@{ub}

Well... As I've said, pEditor is just a testbed for the textediting class for MUI that I've have created, so don't expect pEditor to become a fully featured texteditor.
Nevertheless, I have some ideas to improve it:

- ARexx port.

- Maybe multiple documents loaded at once (a la webPlug's style)... maybe.

- Since it's relatively easy, maybe I'll add the possibility to load/save recorded macros. Does it worth the work ?

- I'm considering to write a simple syntax parser for email messages, since a lot of people seems to use pEditor for this. It would be as a "demo" of the parsing habilities of the class...

pEditor can grow a lot... I'm still thinking about it.

As for the class goes, there are a lot of improvements planned. Don't ask me when, please, when they're done, they will be done :)

- Add the undo/redo system.

- Detecting the cursor position where the user drops another MUI object into the class.

- Configurable keys (currently they are fixed).

- Columnar block/cut/copy/paste.

Actually, the list is quite longer, since a class like this can always be improved in some way.

Things that are unlikely to be implemented:

- "Soft" word wrap.

- Support for non-proportional fonts.

@endnode

