@node LICENSING "licensing"

@{b}@{u}Using pEditor in your programs@{uu}@{ub}

While the class is intended for pEditor and webPlug v2+, I'm open to share it with other programmers. There are some things to consider:

- pEditor is free, the MUI class is not. Contact me for details.

- The class will not be available (in an inmediate future) as an standard MUI "mcc" class. There are strong reasons for this to be this way, and again, this will not change in the near future.
  pEditor will be available as a shared library. It's usage is very very easy (actually, just open the library and start using it as any other MUI class). Future releases of pEditor will make use of the library (in this version, the class is hardcoded into the executable, of course).

- Keep in mind that the pEditor is designed to be used as a source code editor class, so some things are unlikely to be implemented. Take a look at @{" The future " link future}.

I'm currently working on creating some examples in C and AmigaE, and writting some developer information on how to use pEditor.
@endnode

